parameters: \N<Segi>Congratulations, Irime-san.
\N<Irime>Ah, thank you. It seems I've managed to survive another day.

\N<Segi>Rame-chan was worried about you too... It's a relief, to say
the least.
\N<Irime>That's right, now it's your turn.

\N<Irime>As I've said before, your enemy Hojiko is a merchant. He's
the type who can be swayed by profit, for better or worse.

\N<Irime>In other words, there might be room for negotiation if you
dangle money or benefits in front of him.
\N<Segi>Negotiation...?
\N<Irime>Yes, of course, but you'll need something of value for that.
\N<Segi>...
\N<Boy>Hm? Isn't that Riia over there?
\N<Riia>Ah...

\N<Boy>What are you doing in a place like this? It's fine to wander
around, but have you finished that assignment yet?
\N<Riia>Y-yes... it's finished.
\N<Segi>...?
\N<Segi>You must be Fubii... Are you friends with Riia?

\N<Boy>Friends? Me and him? Ahaha, yeah, that's right. We're
friends, aren't we?
\N<Riia>Y-yeah...
\N<Segi>...
\N<Boy>I see, so you're Riia's mother. I had no idea.

\N<Boy>Riia's quite the bad boy, not telling me he had such a
beautiful mother sooner.
\N<Riia>Th-that's...
\N<Segi>And you are? Why are you here in this place?
\N<Boy>Heh, isn't it obvious? Today was the day of my match.

\N<Segi>A match... You're being forced to participate in the
training corps too, even though you're about the same age as
Riia...

\N<Boy>Don't get it wrong, lady. Didn't I tell you I'm not from
this town? I joined the training corps of my own volition.
\N<Segi>What...!?

\N<Boy>Heh, of course I won today's match too. And my opponent was
a full-grown adult. It wasn't even fun at all.

\N<Segi>You joined on your own? Why would you do something like
that...

\N<Boy>More importantly, I heard you're participating in the
training corps too, right? So it's either you or the person
you fight who will be my next opponent, depending on who
wins?
\N<Segi>Me... against you!?
\N<Boy>Heh, it's not surprising, right? That's the rule after all.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Boy>Heh, well then. If we talk any more, you might find out my
weakness, so I'm off.
\N<Boy>Riia, aren't you going to say goodbye?
\N<Riia>G-goodbye...
\N<Boy>Oh yeah, lady. I forgot to say one last thing.

\N<Boy>Heh, if I win, you'll let me have my way with you. Looking
forward to it.
\N<Segi>Wha...!?
A

\N<Riia>Mama... do your best. I'm cheering for you! I'll cheer you
on with all I've got!

\N<Rame>Hello, Segi-san. Ah, um... Aren't you with Riia-chan today?
If it's okay, could you... p-please give my regards to him?
